The U.S. Government and the Republic of South Sudan will be hosting an International Engagement Conference for South Sudan in Washington D.C. on December 14th and 15th. The purpose of the conference is to support South Sudan as it shares its vision for development and economic growth priorities. The conference will bring together international partners, private sector and civil society leaders to discuss collaboration and investment opportunities in South Sudan. Key international partners, including the governments of United Kingdom, Norway, Turkey, the European Union, the African Union, the United Nations, the World Bank, and others, are co-sponsoring the conference.